FBIS3-9122 "dreeu054_p_94006" FBIS-EEU-94-054 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Mar 1994 POLAND New Political Coalition Founded in Slupsk LD1903213194 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network in Polish 2100 GMT 19 Mar 94 LD1903213194 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network Language: Polish Article Type:BFN [Text] Representatives of six political groups in Slupsk--Solidarity, the Christian-National Union, the Polish Democracy Party, the Movement for the Republic, Center Accord, and the Polish Peasant Party-Peasant Accord--have created an electoral bloc under the name "Christian-Independence Forum." The alliance is opting for the development of local self-governments and is expressing itself in favor of the decentralization of the state.
